  "texts": [
    "Q-learning is an off-policy algorithm that learns the optimal policy regardless of the agent's current policy.",
    "In Q-learning, the agent updates its action-value function using the Bellman equation, which expresses the optimal value of a state-action pair as the immediate reward plus the discounted future value of the next state-action pair.",
    "The agent iteratively updates the Q values using this equation until the optimal Q values converge.",
    "Building upon the foundations of Q-learning, DQN is an extension that combines reinforcement learning with deep learning techniques 15.",
    "It uses a deep neural network as an approximator to estimate the action-value function Q(s, a)."
  ],
